In the voice of the seventh angel, the end of the sixth age and the beginning of the seventh is announced.

407
01:26:21,890 --> 01:26:26,790
In the two martyrs, two types of martyrdom are recognized, and he says that the third woe has come.

408
01:26:27,384 --> 01:26:33,355
By mentioning the second coming, the birth of Christ is narrated in the open temple of God in heaven, which is the Church.

409
01:26:33,355 --> 01:26:39,229
The Church is said to have emerged victorious from the battle with the dragon by following in the footsteps of its head.

410
01:26:39,229 --> 01:26:41,333
In the fourth book, the beast is discussed.

411
01:26:41,333 --> 01:26:45,934
It is said to have seven heads and ten horns, symbolizing opposition to Christ and the Church.

412
01:26:45,934 --> 01:26:51,857
Although it is said to bear the signs of the Antichrist for a time, the patience and wisdom of the saints must endure it.

413
01:26:51,857 --> 01:26:55,577
The mark or name of the beast, or its number, is advised to be investigated.

414
01:26:55,577 --> 01:27:01,401
After this, the Church is described as steadfast in the elect, named under the Lamb, and numbered with a sacred number.

415
01:27:01,401 --> 01:27:05,611
Christ is also depicted differently, sitting on a white cloud, crowned, with a sickle.

416
01:27:05,611 --> 01:27:12,757
It mentions the seven plagues and reports the victory of the saints, along with the Jews' enduring hardness of heart and incomparable persecution.

417
01:27:12,757 --> 01:27:21,665
It foretells the future damnation of the harlot, described with the deceitful attire of a woman, symbolizing both worldly power and hidden wickedness, with seven heads and ten horns.

418
01:27:21,665 --> 01:27:25,728
In the fifth book, the same coming of Christ is suggested in a different narrative.

419
01:27:25,728 --> 01:27:30,378
He is said to descend from heaven as an angel, illuminating the earth with his power and glory.

420
01:27:30,378 --> 01:27:36,398
Babylon is mentioned to be destroyed, foretold to fall with many symbolic names, and shown to be punished for its iniquity.

421
01:27:36,398 --> 01:27:41,440
The dignity of the saints is remembered among the elders, the wedding of the Lamb, and the clean linen.

422
01:27:41,440 --> 01:27:50,887
Here, Christ is described as wearing a diadem, sitting on a white horse, battling the beast, and binding the devil with chains for 1,000 years so that he loses the power to deceive the nations.

423
01:27:50,887 --> 01:27:54,215
He is seen sitting on a white throne as the form of future judgment.

424
01:27:54,215 --> 01:28:02,144
The second coming of Christ is again mentioned when a new heaven and new earth are described, with the renewal of the elements and the new Jerusalem as the bride.

425
01:28:02,927 --> 01:28:06,994
The Lamb, the foundation of the patriarchs and apostles, is secured by promises.

426
01:28:06,994 --> 01:28:14,009
It is said to possess the reward, to be illuminated by the light of the Lamb, to drink from the fountain of life, and to enjoy its vision.

427
01:28:14,009 --> 01:28:19,143
Therefore, He often refers to Himself as Alpha and Omega to signify the Trinity of one divine nature.

428
01:28:19,143 --> 01:28:21,685
His future Gospel seems consistent with this book.

429
01:28:21,685 --> 01:28:27,581
By repeatedly mentioning the seven churches, He clarifies the book's purpose and announces His coming to the Church.

430
01:28:27,581 --> 01:28:36,070
Given the length of this work, some may complain about its supposed length, while others, passionate about divine law or reading, may demand more from its great depth.

431
01:28:36,070 --> 01:28:43,950
As I debated between the impatient and the eager, I feared that excessive length might bore some, while brevity might seem envious for withholding details.

432
01:28:43,950 --> 01:28:55,489
Thus, guided by the Lord, I aimed to balance my style, spending more words on the obscure parts and fewer on the clear ones, ensuring I neither deprive the hungry of what they seek nor offend the knowledgeable with my boldness.

433
01:28:55,489 --> 01:29:04,537
I admit that I have not rendered as much service as the lofty dignity of the mysteries required, but have provided as much as my limited abilities, with divine help, could offer.

